1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:04,610
[Disclaimer: This series is entirely fictional
and solely for entertainment purposes

2
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:08,770
with no association or reference
to any individuals, places, or events;

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:12,710
there may be inappropriate behaviors
and vulgarity based on the character's persona;

4
00:00:12,740 --> 00:00:14,980
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:16,329 --> 00:00:18,410
Is there any conflict of interest

6
00:00:18,620 --> 00:00:20,890
behind your last prophecy?

7
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:21,670
Ritt,

8
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:24,190
you've already thought about it, right?

9
00:00:24,690 --> 00:00:25,870
I think...

10
00:00:25,890 --> 00:00:27,140
I'm going to quit.

11
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:28,320
Why?

12
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:29,990
I think this is going too far.

13
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:31,370
Can you help me lift it?

14
00:00:33,330 --> 00:00:34,540
We are stuck inside!

15
00:00:34,690 --> 00:00:35,690
Open the door, please!

16
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:37,380
- You must get married!
- You must get married!

17
00:00:37,410 --> 00:00:39,040
- Get married?!
- Get married?!

18
00:00:39,590 --> 00:00:41,550
Bow to each other

19
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:44,910
to combine two hearts into one.

20
00:01:18,810 --> 00:01:21,490
[Mother]

21
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:37,009
I'll call you back later.

22
00:01:44,670 --> 00:01:45,620
Who called you?

23
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:47,590
My mom.

24
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:50,100
Why don't you talk to her?

25
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:54,240
Have you told your mom

26
00:01:54,940 --> 00:01:56,000
that you're married?

27
00:01:58,410 --> 00:01:59,890
You've been sneaky
about this since last night.

28
00:02:00,270 --> 00:02:01,780
Who said it was just a fake marriage, huh?

29
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:06,560
Last night was just pretend...

30
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:08,710
wasn't it?

31
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,020
It hurts!

32
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,130
You like it rough, don't you?

33
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:17,030
No problem!

34
00:02:17,890 --> 00:02:19,670
Hey, what?!

35
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,480
Do you think I can't fight back? Huh?

36
00:02:23,829 --> 00:02:24,520
Come on!

37
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:27,420
Ouch!

38
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:37,390
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

39
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:41,710
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

40
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:44,050
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

41
00:02:44,070 --> 00:02:49,590
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

42
00:02:50,210 --> 00:02:54,410
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

43
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:58,079
♫Slightly out of line,♫

44
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:02,530
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

45
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:06,870
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

46
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:10,950
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

47
00:03:10,980 --> 00:03:16,280
♫And I believe our love has power♫

48
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:20,370
♫I believe the love of us♫

49
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:27,770
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

50
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:34,290
How was last night?
Did you sleep well?

51
00:03:35,990 --> 00:03:37,090
Yes, I did.

52
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:38,680
I slept...well.

53
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:40,960
Oh, who was on the bed
and who was on the floor?

54
00:03:41,130 --> 00:03:42,270
Hey, Grandpa!

55
00:03:42,470 --> 00:03:43,710
Why did you ask that?

56
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:45,579
It's their private matter.

57
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:47,780
This morning,

58
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,860
the food I prepared is all auspicious.

59
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:54,710
Here is a fish, which means
prosperity and happiness.

60
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:56,310
And here are stir-fried longevity noodles,

61
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:58,850
which make you live a long life.

62
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,250
And this is...

63
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,230
Here.

64
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:03,890
Come on, come on. Hurry up.

65
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,800
Here, a century egg.

66
00:04:07,850 --> 00:04:09,020
What does this one mean?

67
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:14,130
A house full of children
and grandchildren.

68
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:17,519
- Oh, Itthi.
- Be careful, Itthi.

69
00:04:18,910 --> 00:04:22,140
Wasn't getting married supposed to help?
Why is he still like this?

70
00:04:22,910 --> 00:04:24,690
I drank it too quickly.

71
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:25,630
It's okay now.

72
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:29,570
Don't be careless.
You should take extra care of yourself.

73
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,280
Yeah.

74
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,220
Wasn't marriage
supposed to improve his luck?

75
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:33,220
- Yeah!
- This is not acceptable.

76
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,470
I have to call the feng shui masters
to recheck your fortune

77
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:38,159
and see if we should hold more ceremonies.

78
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:40,180
I would like to introduce
a fortune teller to you.

79
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:41,780
- Who?
- Who's that?

80
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:43,820
Here he is.

81
00:04:47,909 --> 00:04:48,690
Do you mean Ritt?

82
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,760
You mean Ritt, right?

83
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:55,250
I can read fortunes a little, Grandma.

84
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:58,300
Wait, wait, wait. I know it.
A few days ago,

85
00:04:58,380 --> 00:05:01,200
he said he tells fortunes using stones, right?

86
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,280
They're runestones, Grandpa.

87
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:04,640
Oh, it's strange.

88
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:07,010
I like something strange like this.
I've never experienced it before.

89
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:09,460
If so, you have to tell
our fortunes, Ritt.

90
00:05:09,890 --> 00:05:12,480
Oh, that's nice.

91
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:15,130
- I want you to read my fortune.
- Oh, how strange. Reading by stones.

92
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,200
Show me. How can you read it?

93
00:05:19,230 --> 00:05:21,710
Pick up three stones, Grandma.

94
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:27,680
Mmm. Hey, nice color.

95
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:37,250
[Prosperity, gift, happiness]

96
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:40,140
Are they all good?

97
00:05:40,470 --> 00:05:42,650
The first stone, Fehu,

98
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:44,390
means prosperity.

99
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:48,570
The second stone, Gebo,

100
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,920
means gift.

101
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:53,350
And the last one,

102
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:56,230
Wunjo, is the stone of happiness.

103
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:58,590
That's great!

104
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,290
Well, after he said they were great,

105
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:03,820
- you are beaming from ear to ear, huh?
- Of course.

106
00:06:03,850 --> 00:06:06,080
These stones look like
they really have energy.

107
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,370
You should try, Grandpa.

108
00:06:08,460 --> 00:06:09,690
How?

109
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:14,180
Whoa, shaking?
Are they fortune sticks?

110
00:06:15,590 --> 00:06:17,520
- What should I do?
- Pick three stones like Grandma did.

111
00:06:17,530 --> 00:06:19,000
Three pieces.

112
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:24,290
Quit the act.

113
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,630
Hey, I need to concentrate.

114
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,690
Doing this is about belief, right?

115
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,930
If you believe, the results will be great.

116
00:06:31,050 --> 00:06:31,790
Here you go.

117
00:06:33,450 --> 00:06:35,230
Ah, they must be great. Yeah.

118
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,170
[Hail: destruction and loss,
Necessity: scarcity and sorrow,

119
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,400
Ice: stillness and coldness]

120
00:06:42,650 --> 00:06:43,420
How is it?

121
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:44,780
Are they nice?

122
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:48,760
Yeah, quite nice, Grandpa.

123
00:06:49,340 --> 00:06:50,170
But...

124
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:52,480
a little bit less than Grandma's.

125
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,210
Are you a quack fortune teller?

126
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,340
Hey, Itthi.

127
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:01,610
You should get your fortune told, too.

128
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:03,110
I'd rather not.

129
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,840
Let it happen when there are only two of us.

130
00:07:05,020 --> 00:07:06,200
I'm afraid you'll know it all.

131
00:07:07,770 --> 00:07:10,660
Are you keeping secrets from me now?

132
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,980
Ritt, go read his fortune.

133
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,930
Then tell me. I'm worried about him.

134
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:17,100
This one

135
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,040
always has good fortune, Grandma.

136
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:21,030
Oh, I see!

137
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:22,610
That's right, Grandma.

138
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:24,640
Fortune can't touch me.

139
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,990
Oh, such a show-off.

140
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:29,780
He is such a show-off
because you raised him.

141
00:07:32,159 --> 00:07:35,720
I'll have to leave after breakfast.

142
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:38,020
I'll come visit you next time.

143
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:39,460
Where are you going?

144
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:41,430
I'll go back to my condo.

145
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,670
No. No, you can't!

146
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:44,400
Hey, even though it's a fake marriage,

147
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:46,900
it doesn't mean that's over.

148
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,510
You have to stay together for four months.

149
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:50,470
Four months?!

150
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:52,460
According to what the feng shui masters said,

151
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:53,430
right?

152
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:54,940
Stay here with Grandma, please.

153
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:06,200
You don't have to wait for me.

154
00:08:06,910 --> 00:08:08,390
I need to pack lots of things.

155
00:08:08,810 --> 00:08:09,930
It may take a lot of time.

156
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:12,800
I have to go to the office with Grandpa.

157
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,170
I'll pick you up this evening when I'm done, okay?

158
00:08:16,110 --> 00:08:17,200
You can come whenever you want to.

159
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:19,150
I'm not going to run away.

160
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:20,890
Even if you run away,

161
00:08:21,330 --> 00:08:22,810
I'll keep looking for you until I find you.

162
00:08:25,850 --> 00:08:26,410
Wait.

163
00:08:27,710 --> 00:08:28,590
Forgetting something?

164
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:32,669
No.

165
00:08:36,929 --> 00:08:37,929
What?

166
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:41,250
The deities will find out

167
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:42,650
that our marriage is fake.

168
00:08:43,909 --> 00:08:45,400
Kiss me on the cheek first,

169
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:48,220
so they believe we're a real couple.

170
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:57,160
I'm leaving.

171
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:43,910
Yes, Mom.

172
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,400
Didn't you go home last night?

173
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,140
I dropped some stuff off
at your condo.

174
00:09:47,770 --> 00:09:48,530
Oh!

175
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:52,670
Last night,
I stayed at my friend's house.

176
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,630
I needed to finish my project.

177
00:09:54,830 --> 00:09:57,590
It took so long,
so I just stayed over there.

178
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,600
I didn't see you at the condo,
so I was a bit worried about you.

179
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:02,790
Okay, Mom.

180
00:10:04,450 --> 00:10:05,290
I love you, Mom.

181
00:10:05,410 --> 00:10:07,680
I love you, too.
Don't forget to take care of yourself.

182
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:29,550
According to the energy,
wind direction, and chi,

183
00:10:29,970 --> 00:10:33,920
this building faces
the southeast wind directly.

184
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:35,720
It's called the Hungry Tiger Wind.

185
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,290
Oh.

186
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,100
The downside of this wind is

187
00:10:38,290 --> 00:10:40,000
its unstable energy,

188
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:42,500
which makes people easily upset

189
00:10:42,530 --> 00:10:44,520
and lazy.

190
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:48,140
- Oh, how can we fix that?
- A lot needs to be fixed.

191
00:10:48,170 --> 00:10:52,330
There has to be
a wide stream in front of it

192
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:55,230
to slow down the wind.

193
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:58,640
The tiger will enjoy the water
instead of being hungry.

194
00:10:58,770 --> 00:11:00,310
Okay, just follow that.

195
00:11:00,730 --> 00:11:01,320
Yes.

196
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:03,700
We worked so hard on the design,

197
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:06,020
only to end up following
a feng shui master, right?

198
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:08,690
For the second building, this one is nice.

199
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,520
There is water energy in the front.

200
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,730
It's like a dragon drinking water.

201
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:16,720
All the fronts of the building,
from top to bottom,

202
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,150
have to be mirrors

203
00:11:18,270 --> 00:11:22,490
to fully bring the water
and the dragon energy into the building.

204
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:25,540
After the energy is brought,
we need to build a base.

205
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:28,800
You need to use only quartz or white jade

206
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,700
to accumulate the energy.

207
00:11:30,910 --> 00:11:34,670
Just like collecting energy
to form an energy pit.

208
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,550
That will help the people in this building

209
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:37,660
not lose their energy.

210
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,010
Their energy will be full.

211
00:11:39,050 --> 00:11:42,080
Well, let's go with that.

212
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:44,120
But we've already ordered the stones.

213
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,710
We can order them again.

214
00:11:45,770 --> 00:11:47,520
We can keep those stones
for other projects.

215
00:11:47,610 --> 00:11:49,080
Okay, let's continue.

216
00:11:49,780 --> 00:11:51,370
For the last project,

217
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:54,110
it stands on the hill,
facing a strong wind.

218
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:57,130
It feels like
we're riding a yawning dragon,

219
00:11:57,170 --> 00:12:02,050
and the strong wind makes
its back unstable.

220
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:05,650
So there has to be
rear support at the back.

221
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,250
It has to be made from black stone

222
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,680
or volcanic stone.

223
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:11,140
So the dragon can rest there.

224
00:12:11,170 --> 00:12:13,300
Then this building's energy will stabilize.

225
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:16,850
Luck and money won't slip away.

226
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:18,190
That's it.

227
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,750
What do you think, Itthi?

228
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,100
I think that...

229
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:26,910
many people here
might consider it a superstition,

230
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,430
but for me,

231
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,960
I consider it

232
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,920
a design that understands nature,

233
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:34,310
people, and the environment.

234
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,670
It's the same scientific principles,

235
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:38,350
just a different language.

236
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:40,940
The younger generation

237
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,210
- already believes in this stuff.
- It's true.

238
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:46,450
Actually, it can be proved
since it's about science,

239
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,700
just conveyed through belief.

240
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:51,510
Hmm...and it works.

241
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:58,000
Oh, wow.

242
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:01,630
This is it.

243
00:13:01,850 --> 00:13:04,200
It's about building credibility
according to marketing principles.

244
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,270
Whether it's accurate or not,
it's another point.

245
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:08,810
Just having a distinct style.

246
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,600
Have you ever heard this?

247
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:11,960
"I have style;

248
00:13:12,310 --> 00:13:13,280
therefore, I am."

249
00:13:15,110 --> 00:13:17,770
This fortune teller is ready
to open her office.

250
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,620
I think something is missing.

251
00:13:20,950 --> 00:13:22,470
We need branding to make it memorable.

252
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,860
Now, we already have
Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master.

253
00:13:24,990 --> 00:13:25,890
What will you be?

254
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:28,470
What should I be, Pure?

255
00:13:29,490 --> 00:13:30,790
What kind of cards do you use?

256
00:13:30,980 --> 00:13:32,680
Romani cards, poker cards,

257
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,580
Promayarn cards, or Oracle cards?

258
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:36,000
I use picture cards.

259
00:13:36,390 --> 00:13:37,730
Well...

260
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:40,100
I combined multiple fields

261
00:13:40,290 --> 00:13:43,570
and used pictures
to visualize the prophecies.

262
00:13:44,810 --> 00:13:46,840
Ployplern, the Pictura Master.

263
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:48,150
"Let the pictures tell your fortune."

264
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:56,330
I liked your summary at the conference.

265
00:13:56,800 --> 00:14:00,450
These modern designers
and engineers believe in Western ideas.

266
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:02,100
They will finally understand

267
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:04,710
that this is not just a superstition.

268
00:14:05,330 --> 00:14:06,190
Yes, Grandpa.

269
00:14:07,410 --> 00:14:08,500
What about your study?

270
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:09,750
How is it?

271
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:10,600
Hmm?

272
00:14:11,010 --> 00:14:12,450
Now, I'm deciding

273
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,850
which university I should go to.

274
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:18,120
Get your degree fast
so that you can help me with my work.

275
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:20,710
If that's all for today,

276
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,360
let me go pick up Ritt.

277
00:14:22,580 --> 00:14:25,030
He's packing things at his condo.

278
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:26,230
Sure.

279
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:28,470
And will you go back
to have dinner with Grandma and me?

280
00:14:29,860 --> 00:14:31,330
You two can have your dinner.

281
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:34,190
Ritt and I will find something to eat
before heading back home.

282
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:36,030
What a newlywed couple.

283
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:36,960
Fine.

284
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:40,710
I can go back and have an old cup
of fermented bean curd with your grandma.

285
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:46,650
Are you sure
you won't change your mind, Itthi?

286
00:14:46,930 --> 00:14:47,810
Yes, Grandpa.

287
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,910
So don't be home late, okay?

288
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,040
Drive safely.

289
00:14:51,070 --> 00:14:51,670
Let's go.

290
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:53,600
- Let's go.
- Get home safe, Grandpa.

291
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:54,810
Of course.

292
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,410
What you're waiting for
may still be there.

293
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,650
It's just waiting for the right time.

294
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:20,590
Don't rush to win him back.

295
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:23,440
You'd better try
to return to yourself first.

296
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:25,290
No matter what happens,

297
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:27,370
don't lose yourself.

298
00:15:31,710 --> 00:15:34,830
Sometimes, love isn't about
making the right choice,

299
00:15:35,340 --> 00:15:38,640
but about someone
who stays with you, even when you're lost.

300
00:15:41,890 --> 00:15:43,380
Every breath

301
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:45,110
is a new beginning.

302
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:47,480
That's not bad at all.

303
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:49,270
My naughty little sister.

304
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:54,800
Is that everything?

305
00:15:55,940 --> 00:15:56,550
Yes.

306
00:16:01,020 --> 00:16:02,840
Can I drop by the bar first?

307
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:04,990
I haven't been there for days.

308
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:06,800
Sure.

309
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:08,920
But don't get drunk,

310
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:11,060
or you won't make it through tonight.

311
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,140
What do you mean?

312
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,500
Come on, let's get in the car.

313
00:16:42,330 --> 00:16:43,890
Why are there so many people here?

314
00:16:44,230 --> 00:16:45,370
I told you already

315
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,090
that this bar is going to go viral.

316
00:16:49,210 --> 00:16:50,790
Whoa!

317
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:53,400
What a magnificent outfit, Ployplern.

318
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,800
Please call my name correctly.

319
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:58,770
I'm Ployplern, the Pictura Master.

320
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,800
Whoa!

321
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,190
If so,

322
00:17:01,610 --> 00:17:03,690
Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master,

323
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,140
is going to be out of favor.

324
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,329
Being a fortune teller
is exhausting, isn't it, Ritt?

325
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:11,800
Here you go.

326
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:13,430
A cold, fresh drink

327
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,000
for your courage.

328
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,200
Hey, Ritt.

329
00:17:19,930 --> 00:17:22,150
Do you want to test how accurate she is?

330
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:24,000
Sure.

331
00:17:24,690 --> 00:17:25,760
Here.

332
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:29,040
Shuffle the cards, then pick two.

333
00:17:29,210 --> 00:17:30,210
Pick with your left hand.

334
00:17:31,020 --> 00:17:31,910
Okay.

335
00:17:43,630 --> 00:17:46,000
The hidden truth behind the mask.

336
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:50,800
The grindstone.

337
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:52,420
What does it mean?

338
00:17:53,130 --> 00:17:55,620
The secret that may hurt you.

339
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:06,590
Ah,

340
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:10,390
I guess
these two fortune tellers can't coexist.

341
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:12,680
Now, I have to make sure
your schedules don't overlap.

342
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:15,000
If they want a specific fortune teller,
they can follow the schedule.

343
00:18:15,790 --> 00:18:18,310
Hey, don't use me for free!

344
00:18:18,410 --> 00:18:20,270
I want a share.

345
00:18:20,420 --> 00:18:21,480
Of course,

346
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,320
my dear little sister.

347
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:38,890
It's already done.

348
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,110
Aren't you guys asleep yet?

349
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,640
We've just finished the ritual.

350
00:18:45,210 --> 00:18:47,860
If you'd come here earlier,
we could have prayed together.

351
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:48,760
Right.

352
00:18:50,340 --> 00:18:51,120
That's good!

353
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:53,100
Your fates are bound together,

354
00:18:53,510 --> 00:18:55,750
supporting each other in a good way.

355
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:58,470
It's obvious that your fates are better.

356
00:19:00,810 --> 00:19:03,910
But even though you're married
in order to alter the fate,

357
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:05,310
your fates

358
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:10,110
are still coiled together
in the water's reflection.

359
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:13,980
Mmm, actually...

360
00:19:14,190 --> 00:19:16,970
there are some unresolved issues.

361
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:19,640
I think

362
00:19:20,210 --> 00:19:22,290
you need to travel.

363
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,050
Right.

364
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:27,670
To make the water

365
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:29,850
and the wind flow well,

366
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:33,600
you need to worship these sacred entities.

367
00:19:34,990 --> 00:19:37,410
The great dragon under the sky.

368
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:41,620
The great tree without a man.

369
00:19:42,460 --> 00:19:43,810
- What are they like?
- How?

370
00:19:45,060 --> 00:19:47,030
And...

371
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:49,510
And...

372
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:54,700
And

373
00:19:58,320 --> 00:19:59,660
And...

374
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,490
And...

375
00:20:06,390 --> 00:20:09,720
And...

376
00:20:12,530 --> 00:20:13,370
But...

377
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:14,690
you need to visit all of them

378
00:20:14,710 --> 00:20:17,340
before a full moon day.

379
00:20:17,490 --> 00:20:19,500
Yeah, you need to visit all of them.

380
00:20:19,890 --> 00:20:21,110
You can't miss even one.

381
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:24,060
Yeah, otherwise you're doomed.

382
00:20:26,090 --> 00:20:26,860
Right?

383
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,870
You're so lucky to meet us first.

384
00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:37,220
Are you full already?

385
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:38,600
Yes, Mom.

386
00:20:48,190 --> 00:20:49,020
Hey, what's up?

387
00:20:49,910 --> 00:20:51,190
Are you free today?

388
00:20:53,190 --> 00:20:54,010
What are you going to do?

389
00:20:55,050 --> 00:20:57,000
I would like to ask you out on a date.

390
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:58,410
The bar is closed today.

391
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,590
The electricity authority
will cut the power until 8 P.M.,

392
00:21:00,890 --> 00:21:03,130
so I'm taking this as my day off.

393
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:05,720
I would like to take you
to experience something new with me.

394
00:21:06,510 --> 00:21:09,020
Well, we normally meet at the bar.

395
00:21:09,420 --> 00:21:10,810
Let's meet somewhere else today.

396
00:21:15,260 --> 00:21:15,970
Why not?

397
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:16,990
Okay.

398
00:21:17,410 --> 00:21:18,280
See you.

399
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:22,380
Mom,

400
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,040
I'll go outside today.

401
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:25,670
Where are you going?

402
00:21:26,390 --> 00:21:27,790
Somewhere with a friend.

403
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:28,990
He's coming to pick me up.

404
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:31,050
A friend?

405
00:21:32,010 --> 00:21:32,760
Who?

406
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,200
A friend...

407
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:36,750
A friend of my friend.

408
00:21:52,710 --> 00:21:54,510
Be careful while driving

409
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:57,920
and try to visit all the places
the feng shui masters told you to, okay?

410
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,240
Yes, Grandma.

411
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:01,360
It seems like

412
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:03,210
they're on a honeymoon.

413
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:04,340
Ah, yeah.

414
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:05,800
Oh! By the way,

415
00:22:05,890 --> 00:22:07,970
you should take me
on a honeymoon like them.

416
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,000
Just the two of us like them.

417
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:09,900
The two of us.

418
00:22:09,950 --> 00:22:12,650
Hey, I am one, and you are one,
so how can there be two?

419
00:22:12,690 --> 00:22:13,380
Such nonsense.

420
00:22:13,420 --> 00:22:15,170
Have a happy trip.

421
00:22:16,010 --> 00:22:17,810
It'll be late.

422
00:22:18,740 --> 00:22:19,960
Drive safe.

423
00:22:20,790 --> 00:22:22,620
Don't buy too many things, okay?

424
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:27,450
A scam fortune teller
who impersonates others and makes up stories.

425
00:22:29,330 --> 00:22:30,900
We're leaving now, Grandpa, Grandma.

426
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:32,090
- Good luck.
- We'll bring...

427
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:34,390
good luck to you.

428
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:35,840
Have a safe trip.

429
00:22:35,870 --> 00:22:36,870
Best of luck.

430
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:37,810
Enjoy the trip.

431
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:38,890
Have a safe trip.

432
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:51,100
- Goodbye, Grandpa, Grandma.
- Okay, bye.

433
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:53,220
- Drive carefully.
- Don't drive too fast.

434
00:22:53,910 --> 00:22:55,090
Bye-bye.

435
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:13,840
Oh, wow!

436
00:23:14,010 --> 00:23:15,980
Do you need to dress this well?

437
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:18,200
I'll look dull if I walk beside you.

438
00:23:18,620 --> 00:23:19,620
How?

439
00:23:19,910 --> 00:23:21,390
You told me you were out,

440
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,880
so I just put on
whatever I could at that time.

441
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:26,290
If I had given you time to get dressed,

442
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:28,220
I probably would have seen you wearing a suit.

443
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:31,000
Do you want me to change, huh?

444
00:23:31,580 --> 00:23:33,110
Hey, calm down.
I'm kidding.

445
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:39,390
Please get in the car, oppa.

446
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,950
Why did you bring me here?

447
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:09,600
You don't like it?

448
00:24:10,730 --> 00:24:12,610
Mm...it's pretty strange.

449
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,720
At first, I thought you'd take me to the mall,
enjoy the air conditioning,

450
00:24:16,090 --> 00:24:17,350
watch a romantic movie,

451
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:19,700
or go to a nice restaurant.

452
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,820
I just didn't think of this place.

453
00:24:23,510 --> 00:24:25,000
Have you ever been here before?

454
00:24:26,820 --> 00:24:28,190
How could I ever come here?

455
00:24:29,010 --> 00:24:30,520
I have spent my whole life
in a rehearsal room.

456
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,500
I need to practice,
practice, and practice.

457
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,320
Well, that's good.

458
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,830
I want you to try one thing.

459
00:24:38,490 --> 00:24:41,310
It's another way to
test your ankle condition.

460
00:24:43,370 --> 00:24:44,600
I want to know now.

461
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,380
Ta-da!

462
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:54,860
It's a bicycle.

463
00:24:55,070 --> 00:24:55,990
Bicycle?

464
00:24:56,940 --> 00:24:58,110
What do you mean?

465
00:24:58,690 --> 00:25:00,290
If you can ride a bicycle,

466
00:25:00,470 --> 00:25:02,100
it means your ankle
has already recovered.

467
00:25:02,350 --> 00:25:03,660
So you can return to dancing

468
00:25:03,690 --> 00:25:04,320
or...

469
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:06,280
doing what you love.

470
00:25:07,330 --> 00:25:09,430
What will you do if my ankle hurts?

471
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,010
You can hop on the back of my bike.
I'll ride.

472
00:25:13,630 --> 00:25:14,520
Okay, good.

473
00:25:14,820 --> 00:25:16,080
Let's do this.

474
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:17,780
I'll be the rider.

475
00:25:19,910 --> 00:25:21,100
And you

476
00:25:21,710 --> 00:25:22,840
will be my passenger.

477
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:26,610
If the bicycle sways
from side to side while I am riding,

478
00:25:27,010 --> 00:25:29,700
you need to wrap
your arms tightly around my waist.

479
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:32,740
And if I ride faster,

480
00:25:33,220 --> 00:25:34,820
you need to wrap my waist more tightly.

481
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:36,690
Are you okay with that?

482
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:38,520
I'm heavy, you know?

483
00:25:38,740 --> 00:25:39,740
Can you handle it?

484
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:41,820
No problem at all.

485
00:25:52,620 --> 00:25:54,210
Hey, what? Focus on riding.

486
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,480
Oh, hey! Hold on to me tightly.

487
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:59,070
- Okay?
- Uh-huh.

488
00:25:59,430 --> 00:26:00,700
The bicycle might sway.

489
00:26:01,130 --> 00:26:02,180
Just ride.

490
00:26:07,820 --> 00:26:08,870
Look. It sways.

491
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:11,370
I think the flowers here are so pretty.

492
00:26:11,410 --> 00:26:12,740
I'll come back to see them again.

493
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:16,880
Sorry, sorry.

494
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:19,100
I know it. I know it.
I'm focusing on riding.

495
00:26:28,830 --> 00:26:29,900
Can I sway the bike?

496
00:26:30,090 --> 00:26:30,980
Don't!

497
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:32,680
Okay, I'm not going to do it.

498
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:39,080
Here is fresh, cold juice for you.

499
00:26:40,330 --> 00:26:41,290
Just drink it once.

500
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:43,000
It'll make you feel refreshed,
I guarantee it.

501
00:26:44,350 --> 00:26:46,520
Do you really mean the juice?

502
00:26:46,550 --> 00:26:47,780
Of course, yes.

503
00:26:48,100 --> 00:26:49,410
What did you expect me to say?

504
00:26:56,090 --> 00:26:57,090
What do you think

505
00:26:57,730 --> 00:26:58,730
of our date today?

506
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:00,000
Did I do a good job?

507
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:03,030
It's not even the end of the day.

508
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:04,600
Wasn't it too early to ask?

509
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,700
I just want to make sure

510
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:08,950
you're happy.

511
00:27:10,530 --> 00:27:11,390
Mmm...

512
00:27:12,510 --> 00:27:13,510
Overall,

513
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:16,600
it's alright.

514
00:27:17,730 --> 00:27:18,620
Whoa.

515
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:20,880
Just "alright"?

516
00:27:25,470 --> 00:27:26,380
You know what?

517
00:27:26,970 --> 00:27:29,730
Actually, I really wanted to
bring you stargazing today.

518
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:32,900
Why?

519
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:35,300
I felt that

520
00:27:35,590 --> 00:27:36,980
it's something you can connect with,

521
00:27:37,730 --> 00:27:38,910
but unfortunately,

522
00:27:39,210 --> 00:27:41,300
it's closed for maintenance today.

523
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:46,000
How can it connect with me?

524
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:49,710
Someone famous like you

525
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:52,200
is called a superstar.

526
00:27:53,190 --> 00:27:54,400
So I think by myself that

527
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:57,580
seeing bright beautiful stars

528
00:27:58,350 --> 00:27:59,760
might make you

529
00:27:59,910 --> 00:28:02,720
have more courage to do something new.

530
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,330
Also,

531
00:28:10,700 --> 00:28:11,600
I think that

532
00:28:12,910 --> 00:28:14,400
it must have been really romantic.

533
00:28:18,580 --> 00:28:19,580
Yeah.

534
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:24,450
If I have a chance,

535
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:28,620
I would love to go
stargazing with you for once.

536
00:28:29,450 --> 00:28:30,450
Of course.

537
00:28:30,970 --> 00:28:31,970
Promise me, okay?

538
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:36,390
Uh-huh.

539
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:37,620
I promise you.

540
00:28:52,770 --> 00:28:56,570
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

541
00:28:56,820 --> 00:29:00,890
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

542
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:03,230
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

543
00:29:03,250 --> 00:29:08,770
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

544
00:29:09,390 --> 00:29:13,590
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

545
00:29:13,780 --> 00:29:17,260
♫Slightly out of line,♫

546
00:29:18,020 --> 00:29:21,710
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

547
00:29:21,740 --> 00:29:26,050
♫Try answering
if your world will cross with mine♫

548
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:30,130
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

549
00:29:30,170 --> 00:29:35,570
♫I believe our love will change our♫

550
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:39,550
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

551
00:29:39,590 --> 00:29:43,710
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

552
00:29:43,740 --> 00:29:46,290
♫(But we're gonna try, try, try)♫

553
00:29:46,310 --> 00:29:51,610
♫And I believe our love has power♫

554
00:29:51,850 --> 00:29:55,700
♫I believe the love of us♫

555
00:29:55,840 --> 00:30:04,230
♫Will realign the stars back
to the line where they should be♫

556
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:07,230
♫(And we're gonna try, try, try)♫

557
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,490
Come in, everyone!

558
00:30:13,570 --> 00:30:15,810
The bar is ours today.

559
00:30:16,510 --> 00:30:18,210
Until what time can we
practice here, Ploy?

560
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,570
Whenever we want
because it's closed today.

561
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:23,210
The electricity authority
is fixing the transformer.

562
00:30:23,670 --> 00:30:26,760
The only bad side for today
might be the heat,

563
00:30:27,050 --> 00:30:28,380
but the good side is

564
00:30:28,460 --> 00:30:30,200
we've got a huge practice room

565
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:32,290
for free!

566
00:30:32,590 --> 00:30:33,590
It's pretty good.

567
00:30:33,860 --> 00:30:34,860
There is an open space.

568
00:30:34,950 --> 00:30:35,950
We can practice however we want.

569
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:38,640
Also, it's not that hot here.

570
00:30:38,710 --> 00:30:39,260
Right?

571
00:30:39,290 --> 00:30:40,220
Yes.

572
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:42,560
So, should we start practicing?

573
00:30:43,930 --> 00:30:45,740
Come on! Let's clear the space.

574
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:48,920
Does anyone agree with me?

575
00:30:49,100 --> 00:30:51,190
Is the stuff that we've been practicing

576
00:30:51,410 --> 00:30:52,780
actually useful at all?

577
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:55,240
We get knocked out every time
we enter a competition.

578
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,280
Hey, don't forget that

579
00:30:57,570 --> 00:30:59,200
where there is a will,

580
00:30:59,320 --> 00:31:00,600
there is still a will.

581
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:05,230
At least, we didn't give up on ourselves.

582
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:07,800
That's right.

583
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:10,540
Even though we're not the winners,

584
00:31:10,570 --> 00:31:12,710
we don't stay stagnant.

585
00:31:12,950 --> 00:31:14,620
Those stages

586
00:31:14,660 --> 00:31:16,360
aren't bigger than our dreams.

587
00:31:17,790 --> 00:31:19,060
Come on, let's team up!

588
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:22,720
One, two, three!

589
00:31:22,770 --> 00:31:24,350
Hooray!

590
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:26,200
Let's continue clearing the space!

591
00:31:31,140 --> 00:31:32,140
Let's help one another!

592
00:31:37,790 --> 00:31:39,050
Here it is.

593
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:41,000
Our luxurious dinner.

594
00:31:42,230 --> 00:31:43,030
Come on.

595
00:31:43,190 --> 00:31:44,470
Come on. Let me help you.

596
00:31:46,190 --> 00:31:48,580
I guarantee it's a clean, safe,

597
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:49,890
and hygienic dish.

598
00:31:51,930 --> 00:31:52,690
Really?

599
00:31:54,990 --> 00:31:56,050
I'm going to eat.

600
00:31:57,390 --> 00:31:58,390
Try it.

601
00:32:05,580 --> 00:32:06,450
It's yummy.

602
00:32:06,630 --> 00:32:07,260
What about yours?

603
00:32:08,020 --> 00:32:09,630
Mine is a bit spicy.

604
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:10,650
Do you want to try it?

605
00:32:11,190 --> 00:32:12,000
Sure.

606
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:31,190
Mmm, it's spicy!

607
00:32:31,270 --> 00:32:32,510
- Spicy?
- Uh-huh.

608
00:32:33,410 --> 00:32:34,410
It's really spicy.

609
00:32:34,840 --> 00:32:35,770
Can I have some water?

610
00:32:43,310 --> 00:32:45,080
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

611
00:32:47,500 --> 00:32:48,900
I told you it's spicy.

612
00:32:53,110 --> 00:32:54,030
And...

613
00:32:54,620 --> 00:32:56,240
when will you go back to Korea?

614
00:32:59,940 --> 00:33:01,880
Did you just go straight
to the question without any intro?

615
00:33:02,870 --> 00:33:03,530
Oh,

616
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:07,520
I'm afraid you will go back there
without letting me know.

617
00:33:09,890 --> 00:33:11,340
Do you want me to go back now?

618
00:33:12,820 --> 00:33:14,740
You're probably sick of my face.

619
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:18,610
Can you answer me now,

620
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:20,030
Pitcha?

621
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:27,540
Honestly,

622
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:29,840
I don't know either.

623
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:34,720
I'm just

624
00:33:35,390 --> 00:33:37,800
starting to feel like
I don't want to go back.

625
00:33:39,420 --> 00:33:40,500
Why?

626
00:33:44,290 --> 00:33:45,500
I'm going to tell you the truth.

627
00:33:47,010 --> 00:33:50,130
I'm tired of being someone

628
00:33:51,090 --> 00:33:52,310
everyone admires.

629
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,850
I thought you would say that

630
00:33:59,190 --> 00:34:02,310
you found someone you like,
so you don't want to go back anymore.

631
00:34:04,750 --> 00:34:05,680
Really?

632
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,400
Look.

633
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,000
A mosquito bite.

634
00:34:20,489 --> 00:34:21,409
Please go ahead.

635
00:34:21,909 --> 00:34:22,690
Thank you so much.

636
00:34:22,719 --> 00:34:23,960
Please enjoy.

637
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:35,760
Why did we choose to stay here?

638
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,739
It's the nearest one.

639
00:34:39,300 --> 00:34:41,170
So we can move to another place tomorrow.

640
00:34:42,739 --> 00:34:44,710
There are only a few places left, you know?

641
00:34:57,450 --> 00:34:58,020
Hey.

642
00:34:59,130 --> 00:34:59,920
Are you tired?

643
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:05,000
Go take a shower first...

644
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,210
so that you feel refreshed.

645
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:14,780
That sounds great.

646
00:35:15,310 --> 00:35:16,980
We've traveled the whole day.

647
00:35:55,340 --> 00:35:56,450
Let me shower with you.

648
00:36:00,470 --> 00:36:01,590
Go ahead.

649
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:03,560
Why are you shy?

650
00:36:05,210 --> 00:36:06,740
Hey, who's shy?

651
00:36:07,140 --> 00:36:08,140
I'm not.

652
00:36:10,180 --> 00:36:12,780
If you're not, turn back
and take a shower together.

653
00:39:57,590 --> 00:39:58,690
Three, four...

654
00:40:10,030 --> 00:40:11,710
Hey, the power is on!

655
00:40:11,750 --> 00:40:12,500
Oh!

656
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:13,870
That took so long.

657
00:40:14,190 --> 00:40:15,710
We've been suffering
from the heat for a long time.

658
00:40:16,820 --> 00:40:17,820
Whoa,

659
00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:20,430
did everyone just take a shower?

660
00:40:20,770 --> 00:40:22,030
Oh, Pitcha.

661
00:40:22,290 --> 00:40:23,570
Hey, everyone! Pitcha is here!

662
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:24,450
Oh, my God!

663
00:40:24,530 --> 00:40:25,990
Are you the real Pitcha?

664
00:40:26,220 --> 00:40:27,110
Oh, I'm going to faint!

665
00:40:27,160 --> 00:40:28,030
Oh, dear.

666
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:32,860
Oh-ho!

667
00:40:33,110 --> 00:40:34,110
Whoa.

668
00:40:34,350 --> 00:40:35,100
Oh.

669
00:40:35,640 --> 00:40:38,860
We watch your videos every day, Pitcha.

670
00:40:38,900 --> 00:40:40,760
We can copy all your dance moves.

671
00:40:42,680 --> 00:40:45,930
Hey, Ploy! Can you take a picture
of Pitcha and me?

672
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:47,980
Oh! You should ask him first.

673
00:40:48,190 --> 00:40:50,380
Could you take some pictures
with us, Pitcha?

674
00:40:50,710 --> 00:40:51,590
Of course.

675
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:52,890
Look, the camera is ready.

676
00:40:52,940 --> 00:40:54,330
- Come on.
- Be the photographer, Pure.

677
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:55,370
I'll take pictures for you.

678
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:00,610
Ready?

679
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:04,390
Three, two, one.

680
00:41:04,990 --> 00:41:06,820
One more cute pose, please.

681
00:41:06,970 --> 00:41:09,490
Three, two, one.

682
00:41:10,590 --> 00:41:11,600
So sweet.

683
00:41:12,430 --> 00:41:13,430
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

684
00:41:15,190 --> 00:41:17,730
That's it for today. See you tomorrow.

685
00:41:17,900 --> 00:41:19,320
Go, go. Let's go home.

686
00:41:27,140 --> 00:41:29,390
I wish I could get
my passion back like they do.

687
00:41:30,810 --> 00:41:33,660
Did you dance just for fun,
for a competition, or something?

688
00:41:34,050 --> 00:41:35,910
We formed this group a long time ago.

689
00:41:36,180 --> 00:41:39,080
At first, we danced just for fun after school.

690
00:41:39,300 --> 00:41:40,070
Until...

691
00:41:40,090 --> 00:41:43,320
we saw your videos
from your trainee days in Korea,

692
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:46,960
so we dreamed of becoming
someone like you one day.

693
00:41:48,150 --> 00:41:49,270
Pitcha,

694
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:51,040
if this is possible,

695
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:54,680
could you give us some training?

696
00:41:55,990 --> 00:41:59,530
Everyone must be so happy
to be trained by their idol,

697
00:41:59,620 --> 00:42:03,100
especially if it's someone
who went through hard training like you.

698
00:42:07,820 --> 00:42:09,910
Give it a try. It's just for fun.

699
00:42:11,850 --> 00:42:13,900
Maybe it helps you
rediscover your passion.

700
00:42:19,740 --> 00:42:20,520
Okay.

701
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,260
You mean it?!

702
00:42:22,470 --> 00:42:24,230
You're going to train us, right?

703
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:25,310
Yeah.

704
00:42:27,390 --> 00:42:30,320
I guess I'll have to rename this bar.

705
00:42:31,700 --> 00:42:32,990
I'll change it to...

706
00:42:33,550 --> 00:42:36,270
Magic Move Dance Studio.
What do you think?

707
00:43:03,820 --> 00:43:05,280
You stole a kiss!

708
00:43:06,040 --> 00:43:07,140
Pretending to sleep, weren't you?

709
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:10,070
You want me to keep stealing it, right?

710
00:43:11,690 --> 00:43:13,280
This time, I'm not going to steal.

711
00:43:13,310 --> 00:43:14,310
I'm robbing it!

712
00:43:17,310 --> 00:43:18,480
Stop it!

713
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:20,540
Go take a shower!

714
00:43:21,420 --> 00:43:23,410
How many places do we have to go today?

715
00:43:25,430 --> 00:43:26,840
Only a few places left,

716
00:43:27,190 --> 00:43:28,600
but they're a bit far apart.

717
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,690
So you should take a shower now.

718
00:43:31,900 --> 00:43:33,640
I want to do it with you.

719
00:43:33,850 --> 00:43:35,320
No.

720
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:37,160
No, we'll shower separately.

721
00:43:37,400 --> 00:43:38,620
No.

722
00:43:39,490 --> 00:43:40,490
Let's shower together.

723
00:43:41,430 --> 00:43:42,720
Come on, go take a shower together.

724
00:43:46,020 --> 00:43:47,370
Take a shower with me, please.

725
00:43:54,740 --> 00:43:55,930
Take a shower with me!

726
00:43:56,440 --> 00:43:57,200
Ouch!

727
00:43:58,890 --> 00:43:59,690
Okay, everyone,

728
00:43:59,780 --> 00:44:01,040
follow me, and let's start again.

729
00:44:01,310 --> 00:44:03,560
Do this while squatting down.

730
00:44:04,220 --> 00:44:05,240
"I..."

731
00:44:06,180 --> 00:44:07,180
"Told..."

732
00:44:07,890 --> 00:44:08,890
"You..."

733
00:44:08,940 --> 00:44:09,920
That's right.

734
00:44:10,520 --> 00:44:13,520
"Maybe not yet."

735
00:44:13,560 --> 00:44:14,730
Shrug your shoulders.

736
00:44:15,780 --> 00:44:18,720
"Maybe not yet."

737
00:44:18,750 --> 00:44:19,820
Shrug your shoulders.

738
00:44:20,030 --> 00:44:21,080
Okay, good job.

739
00:44:21,110 --> 00:44:22,750
So now, we're going to practice
that again from the top,

740
00:44:22,770 --> 00:44:23,730
okay?

741
00:44:23,830 --> 00:44:25,830
Five, six, seven, eight.

742
00:44:26,420 --> 00:44:28,670
"I told you..."

743
00:44:29,110 --> 00:44:31,610
"Maybe not yet."

744
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:32,800
Shrug your shoulders.

745
00:44:32,830 --> 00:44:35,710
"Maybe not yet."
Shrug your shoulders.

746
00:44:35,750 --> 00:44:36,480
Okay,

747
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:37,870
let's stop first.

748
00:44:37,900 --> 00:44:40,270
I want to add something
while you're squatting down.

749
00:44:40,300 --> 00:44:42,140
You need to drop your hips
and flick your ankles.

750
00:44:42,170 --> 00:44:44,630
Do this move clearly, okay? Like this.

751
00:44:46,490 --> 00:44:47,920
Yeah, that's right.

752
00:44:48,280 --> 00:44:51,130
It's okay if you do it wrong,
but what I want to see is

753
00:44:52,340 --> 00:44:53,290
your feelings.

754
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,630
It's not just about staying on beat;

755
00:44:56,140 --> 00:44:57,940
it's about the connection between feelings

756
00:44:58,210 --> 00:44:59,210
and movement,

757
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:01,500
and expressing
those feelings through your moves.

758
00:45:02,490 --> 00:45:05,810
Do you mean we have to dance
like we have stories in our heads?

759
00:45:06,100 --> 00:45:06,630
That's right!

760
00:45:06,720 --> 00:45:09,000
Make it feel like a natural movement.

761
00:45:09,220 --> 00:45:11,590
Make the audience feel the emotions.

762
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:16,560
Just do it
from the bottom of your heart.

763
00:45:16,850 --> 00:45:18,460
No matter how normal the movement is,

764
00:45:19,330 --> 00:45:20,480
the audience can feel it.

765
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:24,760
If so, can we try one more time?

766
00:45:25,020 --> 00:45:26,040
Sure, come on.

767
00:45:26,060 --> 00:45:27,900
Ready? I'll play the music for you.

768
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:52,200
Thank you.

769
00:45:53,470 --> 00:45:54,240
Are you tired?

770
00:45:54,890 --> 00:45:55,710
No. I'm okay.

771
00:45:56,540 --> 00:45:58,110
Drink first, so you'll be fresh.

772
00:46:04,890 --> 00:46:05,890
Thank you very much.

773
00:46:11,430 --> 00:46:12,300
Well done. Good job.

774
00:46:13,390 --> 00:46:14,560
After you finish practicing,

775
00:46:14,740 --> 00:46:17,320
I would like to ask everyone
to help me move the tables before leaving.

776
00:46:17,470 --> 00:46:18,700
The bar has an event today.

777
00:46:18,890 --> 00:46:20,150
What's the event about?

778
00:46:20,850 --> 00:46:21,850
It's about adults' business.

779
00:46:22,020 --> 00:46:23,020
Kids aren't involved.

780
00:46:23,550 --> 00:46:25,050
Just focus on arranging the tables.

781
00:46:25,180 --> 00:46:26,050
Okay?

782
00:46:28,380 --> 00:46:29,720
Come on. Let's help each other.

783
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:35,940
What event will take place tonight?

784
00:46:37,110 --> 00:46:40,010
Pure is hosting
a sales-boosting event tonight.

785
00:46:40,860 --> 00:46:41,770
How?

786
00:46:49,150 --> 00:46:49,800
Drink up.

787
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:54,410
Bottoms up!

788
00:46:57,040 --> 00:46:57,970
- Whoa!
- Hey!

789
00:46:58,980 --> 00:47:00,290
Bottoms up, bottoms up!

790
00:47:02,900 --> 00:47:04,360
Bottoms up, bottoms up.

791
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:07,180
[Safe]

792
00:47:07,240 --> 00:47:08,800
- Safe!
- What?! Safe?!

793
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:10,290
- You got 'Safe' again.
- 'Safe' again.

794
00:47:10,940 --> 00:47:11,930
Let's see.

795
00:47:11,960 --> 00:47:13,330
[A big ice cube]

796
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:16,710
Ice, ice.

797
00:47:17,430 --> 00:47:18,250
Set the time.

798
00:47:18,280 --> 00:47:20,810
Four, three, two.

799
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:25,200
Don't, don't.

800
00:47:25,530 --> 00:47:26,330
Do you want to start?

801
00:47:26,400 --> 00:47:27,580
Yes. My turn, right?

802
00:47:30,660 --> 00:47:32,870
One leg!

803
00:47:33,040 --> 00:47:33,990
One leg!

804
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:36,020
One leg, one leg!

805
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:40,010
Don't step out of the paper.

806
00:47:40,890 --> 00:47:42,850
- You're stepping out of it!
- Start the timer.

807
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,840
Wrap your leg around his.

808
00:47:44,870 --> 00:47:46,660
- Start the timer...
- More, more.

809
00:47:46,690 --> 00:47:47,730
Three!

810
00:47:47,790 --> 00:47:49,150
- Three!!
- Four!

811
00:47:49,310 --> 00:47:50,860
Three!
- Five!

812
00:47:50,970 --> 00:47:52,390
Three!

813
00:47:52,470 --> 00:47:54,810
- Three!
- Jeez! It's too long for three.

814
00:47:55,910 --> 00:47:56,980
Did you guys cheat?

815
00:47:57,090 --> 00:47:58,910
- Next, next.
- Next.

816
00:47:58,960 --> 00:48:00,660
Next, next, next.

817
00:48:00,690 --> 00:48:02,410
Next, next.

818
00:48:02,690 --> 00:48:05,210
- One, two, three.
- Three, go!

819
00:48:05,240 --> 00:48:05,960
[Mouth to mouth]

820
00:48:05,980 --> 00:48:07,520
- Hey!
- There you go.

821
00:48:07,970 --> 00:48:10,150
- Mouth to mouth!
- Mouth to mouth!

822
00:48:10,460 --> 00:48:11,140
Mouth...

823
00:48:11,660 --> 00:48:12,920
Mouth to mouth.

824
00:48:15,050 --> 00:48:17,090
You can skip this time.

825
00:48:17,380 --> 00:48:19,700
You just have to drink it all.

826
00:48:23,580 --> 00:48:24,460
Are you afraid?

827
00:48:26,010 --> 00:48:26,960
Someone like me

828
00:48:27,700 --> 00:48:28,550
